                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d250">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Mutual Guarantee (Locarno)/691:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-05-22T16:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 22, 1936—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received May 22—11:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>275. With reference to penultimate paragraph of my 270, May 20, 12 noon, I was
                    informed by a reliable source that information has reached this country during
                    the last day or so that <hi rend="italic">pourparlers</hi> have indirectly been
                    opened by Hitler with Mussolini, the former stressing the preeminence of the
                    German minority question in Czechoslovakia and that the friendship of Italy was
                    more important to Germany than Austria.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bingham</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
